<body>

    <h1>RBC Count Ki Jaankari</h1>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>RBC Count Kya Hai?</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>RBC count</strong>, yaani Red Blood Cell count, ek blood test hai jo aapke khoon mein laal rakt koshikaon (red blood cells) ki sankhya ko maapta hai. Ye koshikayein <strong>hemoglobin</strong> naam ka ek protein istemaal karke aapke phephdon (lungs) se oxygen ko poore sharir mein pahunchati hain.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Normal RBC Range</h2>
        <p>Vayaskon (adults) mein normal range aam taur par yeh hoti hai:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purush:</strong> 4.7 se 6.1 million cells/mcL</li>
            <li><strong>Mahila:</strong> 4.2 se 5.4 million cells/mcL</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Asamaanya Count Ke Kaaran</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>Kam RBC Count:</strong> Yeh <em>anemia</em> (khoon ki kami), vitamin B12 ki kami, andarooni bleeding, ya kidney ki beemari ka sanket ho sakta hai.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Adhik RBC Count:</strong> Yeh <em>dehydration</em>, smoking, dil ki beemari, ya phephdon ki samasya (jaise pulmonary fibrosis) ke kaaran ho sakta hai.
        </p>
    </div>

</body>
